I would agree that the chr for tr substitution isn&#39;t serious enough to 
be considered a type of pathology.  Idiosyncrasy is an appropriate 
term.  Furthermore, in my opinion an idiosyncrasy such as this 
substitution should not be used in writing QS anymore than those with 
actual pathologies should attempt to write their unusual pronunciations 
into QS.

Paige

